          <span class="phase-title">Settings &amp; Safety</span>
        </div>
        <div class="phase-meta"><span>2–4 days</span><span class="chip you">You + Claude Code</span></div>
        <ul>
          <li>Account info, one visibility toggle, delete account (type-to-confirm)</li>
          <li>Report/block — treat as required, not optional, before any real users touch this</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="phase">
        <div class="phase-head">
          <span class="phase-num">PHASE 2</span>
          <span class="phase-title">Release</span>
        </div>
        <div class="phase-meta"><span>3–5 days</span><span class="chip you">You</span></div>
        <ul>
          <li>Soft-launch to a small test group — local creator meetups, musician/filmmaker Discords</li>
          <li>Fix what breaks with Claude Code's help</li>
          <li>Open it up publicly once the loop — profile, Network, chat — feels solid</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="phase">
        <div class="phase-head">
          <span class="phase-num">LATER</span>
          <span class="phase-title">Option 2, Held in Reserve</span>
        </div>
        <div class="phase-meta"><span>Post-launch</span><span class="chip delegate">Delegate (Fiverr)</span><span>~$3,000–6,000+</span></div>
        <ul>
          <li>Projects board, video Posts, Team/Studio premium accounts — the v1.1 list</li>
          <li>Or: hire out anything specific you get stuck on, instead of the whole build</li>
          <li>Your original cost estimates for these are still accurate if you go this route later</li>
